This data collection, based on the Labour Force Survey 2007 ad-hoc module, provides data on the occurrence of accidents at work, work-related health problems and hazardous exposure. In particular this collection aims:
to know the number of cases and days lost because of accidents at work and the number of cases and days lost because of non-accidental work-related health problems;
to analyse the differences in the occurrence of these accidents and health problems by factors linked to the employment characteristics of the worker and factors linked to the employer's characteristics;
to know about the occurrence of factors at work that can adversely affect health.
The LFS 2007 module gives additional value compared to the administrative data collection ESAW (European statistics at work) by:
including the "less serious" accidents (less than four days of absence from work);
analysing the occurrence of accidents at work by the LFS core variables;
enabling a comparison to estimate the reporting levels in ESAW;
specifying the occurrence of accidents not so well covered in ESAW.
The LFS 2007 module gives additional value compared to the administrative data on occupational diseases by:
specifying the frequency of diseases caused by work or made worse by work, irrespectively if the disease is recognised or not as an occupational disease;
specifying the frequency of new emerging types of work-related diseases which are not included in the administrative lists of occupational diseases (especially musculoskeletal and psychosocial health problems);
estimating the burden of work-related diseases in terms of absence from work;
analysing the occurrence of work-related diseases by the LFS core variables.
Full metadata at: http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/cache/ITY_SDDS/EN/hsw_apex_esms.htm

Regional data collected by Eurostat may be divided into 3 major groups, taking into account the source of the data:a) data collected directly from the countries: data on transport infrastructure, stock of the vehicles and road traffic accidents (collected previously - till 2006 - on Excel sheets) is now collected using an on-line application - REGWeb; it is a voluntary data collection; data is collected at NUTS 2, NUTS 1 and NUTS 0 (country) level;b) data calculated by Eurostat based on the data collected directly from the countries: road safety indexes (people killed by million cars and people killed by million inhabitants); Eurostat calculates them using data listed under point a) above and population data (at regional level) available in Eurostat; data at NUTS 2, NUTS 1 and NUTS 0 (country) level;c) data extracted from existing Eurostat's maritime and aviation databases: data on passenger and freight transport performance for maritime and aviation; the data is collected in the framework of legal acts (at seaport/airport level) and then extracted from Eurostat's database with aggregation to NUTS 2, NUTS 1 and NUTS 0 (country) level.
Eurostat also uses the road transport data collected within the scope of another legal act. The 2001 data (extracted at NUTS 3 level from the road database) were analysed mostly through transportation modelling. Currently the modelling is not carried out and the dissemination tables are not updated anymore.
Several tables present historical data and are not updated any more due to the evolution of the data collection (changes of the legal acts). The tables which are no longer updated are marked in the list below in italics.
The regional transport statistics section contains mostly data at NUTS 2, NUTS 1 and NUTS 0 (country) level, but some contain data at NUTS 2 level only. The statistics cover the following tables:
Road, rail and navigable inland waterways networks at regional level (tran_r_net) - data since 1978; update on regular basis;
Stock of vehicles by category at regional level (tran_r_vehst) - data since 1990; update on regular basis; 
Victims in road accidents at regional level (tran_r_acci) - data since 1990; update on regular basis; 
Maritime transport of passengers at regional level (new methodology) (tran_r_mapa_nm) - data since 1997 based on the Directive 2009/42/EC; update on regular basis; 
Maritime transport of freight at regional level (new methodology) (tran_r_mago_nm) - data since 1997 based on the Directive 2009/42/EC; update on regular basis; 
Air transport of passengers at regional level (new methodology) (tran_r_avpa_nm) - data since 1993 based on Regulation 437/2003; update on regular basis; 
Air transport of freight at regional level (new methodology) (tran_r_avgo_nm) - data since 1993 based on Regulation 437/2003; update on regular basis; 
Annual national and international railway goods transport by region of loading and region of unloading (tran_r_rago) - 2005 data based on Regulation 91/2003; next data collection in 2010; 
Annual national and international railway passenger transport by region of embarkation and region of disembarkation (tran_r_rapa) - 2005 data based on Regulation 91/2003; next data collection in 2010; 
Maritime transport of passengers at regional level (old methodology) (tran_r_mapa_om) - data from 1978 to 2002 collected via questionnaires; table no longer updated; 
Maritime transport of freight at regional level (old methodology) (tran_r_mago_om) - data from 1978 to 2002 collected via questionnaires; table no longer updated; 
Air transport of passengers at regional level (old methodology) (tran_r_avpa_om) - data from 1978 to 2002 collected via questionnaires; table no longer updated; 
Air transport of freight at regional level (old methodology) (tran_r_avgo_om) - data from 1978 to 2002 collected via questionnaires; table no longer updated; 
National annual railway transport by loading region and by group of goods (Directive 80/1177/EEC) (1000 t) (rail_go_natlreg ) - data from 1982 to 2002 based on Directive 80/1177; table no longer updated available only under Transport/Railway transport/Railway transport measurement - Goods; 
National annual railway transport by unloading region and by group of goods (Directive 80/1177/EEC) (1000 t) (rail_go_natureg) - data from 1982 to 2002 based on Directive 80/1177; table no longer updated available only under Transport/Railway transport/Railway transport measurement - Goods.
 Road transport of goods - Journeys made by vehicles at regional level (tran_r_veh_jour) - results of the modelling using 2001 data; table no longer updated.

Full metadata at: http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/cache/ITY_SDDS/EN/reg_tran_esms.htm
